The paper deals with the problem of collaborative content caching in a network of base stations, which is a typical problem in the field of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also uses optimization techniques to find the optimal caching policy, which is a common theme in game theory (cs.GT) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also models the caching problem as a Markov Decision Process, which is a common technique in control theory (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
